node.text:
Chicken Pasta Salad and a chance to win a $250 WALMART gift card! #ad 

I’ve teamed up with @walmart and @worldfoodchampionships to create this chicken pasta bowl. Join in on the fun and enter for a chance to win! Get your inspiration on www.walmart.com/cookingchallenge to learn more about the rules and post your creation on FB and instagram using the hashtag #walmartcookingchallenge. Good luck! 

Chicken Pasta Salad Recipe 
Serve 4 

* 2 Boneless Skinless Chicken Breasts, diced 
* 1 Tbsp Olive Oil
* 1 tbsp lemon pepper 
* 1 tsp salt 
* 8 oz whole grain pasta, or gluten-free
* 1 Cup Cherry Tomatoes halved
* 1/4 cup corn 
* 1/4 cup shredded cheese 
* 1/4 Cup Green Olives sliced in half
* 2 cups fresh chopped spinach 

Dressing:
* 2 Tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil
* 2 Tbsp White Wine Vinegar
* 1 tbsp Honey
* 1 tbsp oregano 
* 2 tsp thyme 
* 1 Garlic Cloves pressed or minced
* 1 tsp salt 
* 1/2 tsp pepper 

Directions 
1-  Sauté the diced chicken with olive oil, lemon pepper and salt. Set aside 
2- Cook pasta according to package directions 
3- Meanwhile, chop and setup the other ingredients and make the salad dressing. 
4- Add everything in a large bowl and too with the salad dressing and mix well. 
5- Serve and enjoy!
.
Link in my profile for more details 
https://bit.ly/37IwwPL

node.text:
Turkey Meatballs in Curry Sauce
.
Ingredients
Meatballs
1 pound ground turkey
1 large egg
1 cup panko
4 green onions minced
2-3 cloves garlic pressed
1 1/2 tbsp grated ginger or ginger paste
1 tbsp low sodium soy sauce or coconut aminos
1 tbsp red curry paste
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper
.
Curry Sauce
1 tbsp groundnut oil or peanut oil
1 red bell pepper sliced
½ yellow onion sliced
1 tbsp minced ginger
1 tbsp red curry paste
1 tbsp honey
1 x 13.5 oz can full-fat unsweetened coconut milk
Cilantro for garnish chopped
1/4 cup roasted peanuts chopped
.
Link in my profile if you need step-by-step instructions:
.

https://healthyfitnessmeals.com/healthy-turkey-meatballs/
